title: Knock It Off
description: When the Professor's college roommate sees his old pal's brilliant creations, he decides to cash in on the popularity of the Powerpuffs.

title: Green Wing
description: When volunteering at a retirement home, Buttercup meets an old woman who claims she used to be a superhero.

title: How to Draw Blossom
description: The Powerpuff Girls character designer, Cheyenne Curtis, show you how to draw Blossom.

title: Forced Kin
description: A terrible, evil menace from outer space descends upon Townville. The girls must fight evil with evil so they seek the advice of Mojo Jojo.

title: Bubbles' Beauty Blog But on Video
description: Bubbles' attempt to start her own beauty blog is thwarted by Blossom and Buttercup.

title: Cat Burglar
description: An alarmingly familiar cat burglar terrorizes Townsville.

title: Air Buttercup
description: Buttercup tries to show off her basketball skills in the lunchroom to no avail.

title: Hustlecup
description: When Buttercup loses the Professor's latest invention, she'll have to beat The Gangreen Gang at their own game to get it back.

title: Bubbs and Donny Get the Mail
description: Bubbles and Donny are given their most daring mission ever: get the mail.

title: Monstra-City/Shut the Pup Up
description: Monstra-city: When all the monsters move from Monster Isle to Townsville, it's up to the Girls to keep the peace./Shut the Pup Up: When the Talking Dog witnesses a crime, he moves in with the girls for protection. But the girls soon realize this chatterbox dog is less than the perfect pet.

title: The Tell Tale Schedulebot
description: After Blossom and Buttercup break Schedulebot, they'll do anything to keep the truth from coming out.

title: Superfriends
description: The new girl next door learns it's hard to be best friends with superheroes and soon starts hanging out with the wrong kind of kid, Princess.

title: All Chalked Up
description: Him tricks Bubbles into bringing her chalk drawings to life, who then proceed to wreak havoc in Townsville.

title: Get Back Jojo
description: Mojo goes back in time to try and stop the Professor from having the inspiration for the perfect little girls. Little does he know that in doing so he provides just the spark the young Professor needs.

title: Super Sweet 6
description: Morbucks throws the biggest birthday party of all time, and Blossom is the only one not invited.

title: 5 Reasons You're Actually Buttercup
description: 5 Reasons You're Actually Buttercup.

title: Rock Off Battle Music Video
description: The Powerpuff Girls rock out!

title: Mini Golf Madness
description: Buttercup takes her game winning mini golf ball, in spite of ominous warnings of dire consequences.

title: Helter Shelter/Power Lunch
description: Helter Shelter: Bubbles has a habit of saving helpless animals and the Professor is sick of it. When Bubbles brings a baby whale home, she and her sisters have a whale of a time hiding this new addition./Power Lunch: The Gangreen Gang shoplifts from a mini-mart, shoveling loads of food down their throats as fast as possible. When the girls fire at them with their laser vision, a strange reaction occurs.

title: Ping Pong Z
description: It's "loser does the dishes" when the girls play ping pong in and around Townsville.

title: Clawdad
description: While visiting the lake, Buttercup vows to capture a legendary uncatchable crawdad.

title: Keen on Keane/Not So Awesome Blossom
description: Keen on Keane: It's Valentine's Day and the girls notice that Ms. Keane is all alone. Time for a little matchmaking, but who will be the lucky fella?/Not So Awesome Blossom: When Blossom's attack plans fail one after the other, she loses confidence in herself as the group's leader.

title: The Last Donnycorn
description: When Donny the Unicorn is hunted by a seemingly unstoppable foe, the Powerpuff Girls have to find a way to save him before it's too late!

title: Rebel Rebel
description: The Professor makes new friends, but they may be the wrong crowd.

title: Members Only
description: When the girls try to join an all-male superhero organization, they learn that sometimes supermen aren't so super.

title: Bedtime
description: The girls need to get a good night's rest before family photo day, but they just can't seem to fall asleep!

title: Splitsville
description: The girls learn to appreciate each others's style after having to each fight solo.

title: Summer Bummer
description: When the beach is taken over by the most excellent Bro Sharks, will the Girls be gnarly enough to save the day?

title: How to Draw Buttercup
description: The Powerpuff Girls character designer, Cheyenne Curtis, show you how to draw Buttercup.

title: 5 Reasons You're Actually Blossom
description: 5 Reasons You're Actually Blossom.

title: Film Flam
description: A sleazy director arrives in Townsville to make a film about the Powerpuff Girls. But this Hollywood type wants more out of Townsville than an Oscar-winning film.

title: Who's Got the Power?
description: Extended main title is set to music.

title: Toast of the Town/Divide and Conquer
description: Toast of the Town: When the Mayor rubs Chemical X on his head for hair growth, all of him grows and stomps through Townsville./Divide and Conquer: When the Amoeba Boys learn how to divide, they multiply wreaking havoc as the many amoebas descend upon Townsville.

title: I'll Be Bake
description: Bubbles and Buttercup's good intentions are bad news for the cake Blossom is trying to bake.

title: Him Diddle Riddle
description: The Powerpuff Girls must solve a series of Him's riddles to keep the Professor from having to pay.

title: Stray Bullet
description: In order to save an innocent squirrel, Bubbles gives him a dash of Chemical X, giving him some super squirrel powers.

title: 15 Minutes of Fame
description: When Bubbles' video goes viral, she goes to great lengths to maintain her status as a big-time director.

title: Burglar Alarmed/Shotgun Wedding
description: Burglar Alarmed: A new burglar comes to Townsville and his first robbery is at the house of the Powerpuff Girls?/Shotgun Wedding: The Professor tries to find out what a Lumkins really is.

title: 5 Reasons You're Actually Bubbles
description: 5 Reasons You're Actually Bubbles.

title: Run, Blossom, Run
description: Blossom oversleeps and she'll stop at nothing to make it to school before she ruins her perfect attendance record!

title: A Star is Blossom
description: When Bubbles gets the lead in the school play, Blossom's jealousy consumes her.

title: How to Draw Bubbles
description: The Powerpuff Girls character designer, Cheyenne Curtis, show you how to draw Bubbles.

title: Mojo Builds a Shelf
description: Mojo discovers the only thing more difficult than total world domination is DIY furniture.

title: Blissfully Unaware
description: Bliss uses her telekinetic powers to help the Professor make a more delicious dinner.

title: Power-Noia
description: The girls have become paralyzed by their greatest fears. Who could be behind such an evil trick?

title: Our Brand is Chaos
description: Bubbles and Buttercup make a deal without realizing the consequences.

title: Tagalong
description: Buttercup is tired of Bubbles following her everywhere.
